                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north wall of the central shrine in the Naṭanapādēśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 46: 1115-16 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records the gift of 1 1/2 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> by Tiruva[ṇ*]ṇāmalai Akkaṉ for a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to god Tirukkaṇṇīśvaram-uḍaiya Mahādēva in Śōḻakulavaḷḷinallūr in Paṭṭāṉpākkai-nāḍu in Gaṅgaikoṇḍaśōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. The money was received by Ārū[r*] Tiruva[ṇ*]ṇāmalai Bhaṭṭaṉ.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
